anti war conservatives make a strong case events at stanford anti war conservatives make a strong case facebook twitter email print add to calendar free lance writer and public speaker mary meehan will be presenting the conservative arguments against the us wars interventions and us imperialism she worked in the 1968 presidential campaign of the late senator eugene mccarthy who challenged the vietnam war and in other antiwar campaigns later she was active against abortion and the death penalty a free lance writer for many years ms meehan has written widely on politics and issues of life and death she has won two awards for investigative reporting on eugenics and population control a longtime contributor to human life review she is now a senior editor of that quarterly she also has written for america commonweal inquiry the progressive social justice review and other magazines her op ed pieces have been published in newspapers such as the baltimore sun des moines register los angeles times new york times and the washington post when wednesday november 30 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where tresidder memorial union oak lounge map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags lecture reading international public service sponsor stanford says no to war freeman spogli institute for international studies columbae amnesty international at stanford center for ethics in society contact jdschott stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 298 29835 more info last modified november 28 2011
